High-Level Architecture

CLI Interface → Automation Engine → Plugin System → Cloud APIs
     ↓               ↓               ↓              ↓
Task Runners   Configuration     Extensions     Infrastructure
     ↓               ↓               ↓              ↓
Executors       Templating      Hooks/Events    Provisioning

Component Interaction:

CLI commands trigger automation workflows

Engine loads configuration and templates

Plugin system extends functionality

Task runners execute sequences

Cloud APIs provision infrastructure

Monitoring agents track performance

Folder Structure:


devops-automator/
├── src/
│   ├── cli/              # Command-line interface
│   ├── core/            # Core automation engine
│   ├── plugins/         # Plugin system
│   │   ├── aws/        # AWS automation
│   │   ├── k8s/        # Kubernetes operations
│   │   ├── docker/     # Container management
│   │   └── monitoring/ # Monitoring setup
│   ├── templates/       # Jinja2 templates
│   │   ├── terraform/  # Terraform configs
│   │   ├── k8s/        # Kubernetes manifests
│   │   └── cicd/       # Pipeline definitions
│   ├── utils/          # Utilities and helpers
│   └── config/         # Configuration management
├── scripts/            # Deployment scripts
├── examples/           # Example configurations
├── tests/             # Test suite


Core Features
Multi-cloud Infrastructure Provisioning (AWS, Azure, GCP)

Kubernetes Cluster Management (EKS, AKS, GKE, bare metal)

CI/CD Pipeline Automation (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Jenkins)

Container Registry Management (ECR, ACR, GCR, Docker Hub)

Secret Management (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, Kubernetes Secrets)

Monitoring Stack Deployment (Prometheus, Grafana, AlertManager)

Database Automation (RDS, Cloud SQL, MongoDB Atlas)

Security Automation (IAM, Security Groups, Compliance checks)
└── docs/              # Documentation
